parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Power Master Brake System can cause the brakes to become extremely resistant and difficult to depress, leading to increased stopping distances and a higher risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels hard or spongy
the brakes are difficult to press
the vehicle takes excessive effort to stop
the brakes fail to work intermittently
the brake pedal does not move in emergency braking situations.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty seat belt buckle can lead to the seat belt malfunctioning, which can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle is cracked
the seat belt locks up and traps the occupant
the seat belt fails to restrain the passenger in an accident.
